      "x(i)": "Income of individual i",
      "N": "Total number of individuals",
      "μ": "Mean income"
    },
    "units": "No specific units, as it's a ratio",
    "notes": "Gini coefficient is a measure of income inequality, ranging from 0 (perfect equality) to 1 (perfect inequality)"
